{"ts": "2026-04-21T20:15:46Z", "event": "clarify_critic", "feature": "classify-critical-review-findings-by-class-and-add-b-class-action-surface", "findings": ["Intent clarity HIGH collapses \"what problem\" (clear) with \"what change\" (genuinely unselected across auto-ticket/residue-file/synthesis-appendix \u2014 three qualitatively different mechanisms with different blast radii). AC3 positive form is deferred to planning.", "Scope boundedness HIGH ignores a direct tension between AC1 (\"Classes cover at minimum: fix-invalidating (A), adjacent-gap (B), framing (C)\") and open-question #2 (\"research flagged the ternary as asserted rather than derived; planning must justify the choice\"). AC1 commits the taxonomy; open-question #2 opens it.", "Requirements alignment \"no conflict detected\" ignores requirements/project.md \"Complexity: Must earn its place by solving a real problem that exists now.\" The research itself flags n=1 with explicit Epistemic caveat; adding ternary taxonomy + new action-surface mechanism + classifier-accuracy validation + straddle-case protocol for one observed failure is on its face what this requirement warns against.", "Criticality medium rests on unverified claim that downstream consumers only present output. No grep of consumers was cited. The skill auto-triggers in lifecycle for Complex + medium/high/critical post-plan, making it load-bearing in overnight execution where operator review is absent.", "AC6 (\"skills/critical-review/SKILL.md updated; no regression to Step 4 beyond intended C-class \u2192 Ask routing tightening\") narrowly scopes to one file, but AC3 action-surface mechanism (auto-ticket touches backlog tooling; residue file introduces new artifact type) implies broader code changes. Scope HIGH while AC3 and AC6 may be mutually incompatible is unsupported."], "dispositions": {"apply": 1, "dismiss": 4, "ask": 0}, "applied_fixes": ["Added to research open questions: whether the A/B/C ternary is correct or a different encoding (binary blocking + orthogonal type axis per CVSS / Conventional Comments / peer-review Major/Minor) better serves the B\u2192A non-promotion rule. Flagged AC1-vs-OQ2 phrasing tension for research to surface."], "dismissals": [{"finding_index": 0, "rationale": "Clarify.md \u00a73 intent-clarity rubric is about \"one clear outcome,\" not \"one clear artifact.\" The outcome (class-tagged findings + refuse B\u2192A promotion + no silent dismissal of B-findings) is unambiguous. Mechanism choice is an implementation alternative within scope, not an ambiguous outcome."}, {"finding_index": 2, "rationale": "The ticket value section explicitly acknowledges n=1 (\"the one documented failure,\" \"one observed instance\"). The complexity/value proportionality check is the specific job of specify.md \u00a74 (complexity/value gate), not Clarify. Routing this concern to Clarify would duplicate the Spec-phase gate; letting it run at its designated gate is correct."}, {"finding_index": 3, "rationale": "Verified via grep: zero programmatic consumers of /critical-review output format exist in skills/, hooks/, or claude/pipeline/*.py. All callsites (specify.md:151, plan.md:243, discovery/research.md:128) explicitly \"present synthesis to the user before approval.\" Only test file (test_skill_callgraph.py) references the skill, and that is a callgraph-existence test, not output-format parsing. Medium criticality is grounded; the output-shape-change claim is verified."}, {"finding_index": 4, "rationale": "AC6 literal text: \"skills/critical-review/SKILL.md updated; no regression to Step 4 Apply/Dismiss/Ask behavior beyond the intended C-class \u2192 Ask routing tightening.\" AC6 asserts (a) SKILL.md is updated and (b) Step 4 non-regresses. It does not scope-cap the ticket to only-SKILL.md. AC3 action-surface mechanism is in scope regardless. The critic misread AC6 as a scope cap."}], "status": "ok"}
